descript.abstract: Assessor's parcel data for town of Chatham, MA. Developed from existing digital data.

idinfo.accconst: This digital parcel data layer is considered to be in the public domain and will become accessible for download and display from the MassGIS website: http://www.mass.gov/mgis

dataqual.logic:
This parcel layer contains discrete, non-overlapping polygons for each property. Adjacent polygons with common ownership and a single tax record have been retained in the "OthLeg" layer that accompanies this TaxPar layer, and dissolved into single parcels in this TaxPar layer. Some non-adjacent parcels may be represented by multi-part polygons where they share common ownership and a single tax record. Public right of ways exist as polygons, not null space. Linework associated with private ROWs are retained in the "OthLeg" layer. Water polygons also representing parcel boundaries have been retained in this TaxPar layer. Additional water features that are not considered parcel boundaries may have been placed in the "Misc" layer that accompanies this TaxPar layer. Easements and other similar non-fee taxable boundaries exist in the 'OthLeg" layer, not the TaxPar layer.
Parcels updates for the years 2014, 2015, 2016 and 2018 performed and mismatches between Assess and TaxPar resolved.

horizpa.horizpar: Data compiled or reviewed for horizontal accuracy over the MassGIS color orthos from 2008/2009; these orthos are known to be +/- 10' horizontal; however, this data set cannot be used to reach authoritative conclusions about the horizontal accuracy of the boundaries depicted. That work requires a licensed land surveyor.

srcinfo.srccontr: Source data is MassGIS Level 0 digital parcel file, in shapefile format.

procstep.procdesc: Existing Level 0 parcel data was converted to MassGIS Level 3 template geodatabase and additional data layers and tables were added.
Spatial accuracy of data was verified using the parcel standard guidelines; town boundary was verified to be coincident with MassGIS Town Boundary layer. Polygon topology was updated and validated.

Multi-part polygons were created where necessary; internal polygon boundaries were dissolved where necessary; polygons representing legal boundaries such as easements or private right-of-ways were created. LOC_ID was updated
CAMA data was matched against parcel data to produce a mismatch report which was reconciled with the help of the town Assessor. Final QAQC tools were run.

Parcels updates for 2014, 2015, 2016 and 2018 completed and CAMA data matched against parcel data to produce a mismatch report which was reconciled with the help of the town Assessor. Final QAQC tools were run.

overview.dsoverv: Tax parcel polygons for Chatam, MA. This data set contains polygons which delineate property ownership in the town of Chatham, according to the assessor's tax maps as of March 2011. It is formatted in compliance with the MassGIS Standard for Digital Parcel Files, Version 2.0. This data set is considered to be MassGIS Level III-compliant and is derived from an upgrade of the previous Level II-compliant version of this same data set.
